/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/runtime/logs/codex-patlas-exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit-step-004-explorer-002.log:2827:/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/runtime/logs/codex-patlas-beyond-de-giorgi-strategizer-step-001.log:1856:Vasseur (2007) showed that full Navier-Stokes regularity follows if the local pressure exponent β exceeds 3/2. Current best: β = 4/3. The gap is 1/6. Can compensated compactness (which places the pressure in Hardy space H^1 for divergence-free velocity fields) close this gap?
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/runtime/logs/codex-patlas-exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit-step-004-explorer-002.log:2828:/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/runtime/logs/codex-patlas-beyond-de-giorgi-strategizer-step-001.log:10176:**Honest limits:** The T_U/T_dS identity lacks a physical mechanism (FDT closes with χ''_dS = χ''_flat exactly — zero modification). It also requires an external factor of ~1/6 to match a₀ and is defeated by lensing. The negative result is what's solid.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/runtime/logs/codex-patlas-exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit-step-004-explorer-002.log:2829:/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/runtime/logs/codex-patlas-beyond-de-giorgi-strategizer-step-001.log:10194:**Why it doesn't work as modified inertia:** No mechanism (FDT gives zero modification), factor of ~1/6 discrepancy in a₀, and falsified by lensing. The identity is mathematical, not physical.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/runtime/logs/codex-patlas-exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit-step-004-explorer-002.log:2830:/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/runtime/logs/codex-patlas-beyond-de-giorgi-strategizer-step-004.log:6907:./promising-findings.md:443:**The result:** The β < 1/6 mass gap threshold is numerically correct but the proof has an irreparable gap. The B² formula step (HessS(v,v) = (β/2N)Σ|B□(Q,v)|²) is NOT an identity at generic Q — it's exact only at flat connections. Follow-up validation found λ_max(H_actual) > λ_max(H_formula) for one-hot perturbations at d≥3. The excess is small (≤ 2.6% at d=2, ≤ 0.5% at d=4), so the conclusion is approximately correct.
